    <fr:title text="Humanoid Robot Learning">Humanoid Robot Learning</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="Benchmarking Humanoid Intelligence">Benchmarking Humanoid Intelligence</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Locomotion tasks: can humanoids move around? Vary terrain, avoid obstacles.</html:p>
    <html:p>Loco-manipulation tasks: can humanoids interact with the environment?</html:p>
    <html:p><fr:link href="https://humanoid-bench.github.io/" type="external">HumanoidBench</fr:link></html:p>
    <html:p>Other manipulation / locomotion benchmarks are too trivial to see drastic performance between algorithms.</html:p>
    <html:p>Learning algorithms struggle with large action space</html:p>
    <html:p>Action space - number of degrees of freedom. Humanoid w/o hands - 19dof, w/ hands 61dof.</html:p>
    <html:p>Idea: decouple dof. Problem want whole body control.</html:p>
    <html:p>Idea: hierarchical learning via domain knowledge. learn to position hands. Extended to library of skills in 
<fr:link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.09366" type="external">Skillblender</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="Scaling sim-to-real learning for humanoids">Scaling sim-to-real learning for humanoids</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
<html:p>Robot / environment:</html:p>
<html:ul><html:li> identify what you can (system identification). </html:li>
    <html:li>what you cannot identify randomize!</html:li></html:ul>
<html:p>Reward</html:p>
<html:ul><html:li>stay away from things you cannot identify.</html:li></html:ul>
<html:p>Simulator: training on cpu takes forever (enter IsaacGym, Mujoco Playground).</html:p>
<html:p>Mujoco Playground limitations</html:p>
<html:ul><html:li>JIT compilation can be slow</html:li>
  <html:li>Computation time scales with the number of potential contacts</html:li>
  <html:li>MJX warp is now supported (100x speedup)</html:li></html:ul>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="Where can we do better?">Where can we do better?</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p><fr:link href="https://younggyo.me/fast_td3/" type="external">Fast TD3</fr:link></html:p>
    <html:p>FastTD3 vs. TD3</html:p>
    <html:ol><html:li>Massively parallel environments</html:li>
    <html:li>Large-batch training</html:li>
    <html:li>Distributional RL</html:li>
    <html:ul><html:li>Discretize value space and output distribution over values</html:li>
      <html:li>Trained with cross entropy loss</html:li></html:ul></html:ol>
    <fr:link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.06316" type="external">Body Tranformer</fr:link>,
    <html:ol><html:li>Inductive bias</html:li>
      <html:li>Computationally efficient</html:li>
      <html:li>Multi-frequency reasoning</html:li>
      <html:li>Localized credit assignment</html:li></html:ol>
    <html:p>Idea: construct graph to connect certain parts of body via embodiment graph. Have attention layers that only attend to neighbors on the graph via the mask being a graph mask.</html:p>
    <html:p>Mask is sparse, allowing much more computationally efficient attention computation.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="A Generalizable Robot Learning Pipeline">A Generalizable Robot Learning Pipeline</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Future directions:</html:p>
    <html:ol><html:li>Vision-based policies</html:li>
<html:li>Real2sim</html:li>
<html:li>Learning from videos</html:li></html:ol>
<html:p>The pipeline</html:p>
<html:ol><html:li>Learn low-level skills</html:li>
  <html:li>Learn to compose skills</html:li>
  <html:li>Finetune with RL</html:li></html:ol>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
</fr:mainmatter>
